#Readme - Connecting Node.js with MySQL via Terminal
In this project, you have created a Node.js script that connects to a MySQL database and interacts with it through the terminal. The script allows you to perform various operations such as displaying all books in the database, displaying books by a given author, displaying all authors, and adding a new author.

Requirements
To run this project, you need the following:

Node.js installed on your system.
A MySQL database with the necessary tables and data.
A .env file in the project directory that contains the necessary database credentials (DATABASE, HOST, USERDB, PASSWORD, PORT). Make sure to update the .env file with your actual database information.
Getting Started

The script will establish a connection to the MySQL database using the provided credentials. Once connected, you will see a list of options in the terminal. Follow the instructions and enter the corresponding option number to perform the desired action.

Options

1. Display all books in the database: This option will retrieve and display all books stored in the database.

2. Display all books by a given author: This option allows you to enter an author's name, and the script will display all books written by that author.

3. Display all authors: Choosing this option will fetch and display all the authors present in the database.

4. Add a new Author: This option enables you to add a new author to the database. You will be prompted to enter the author's name.
